   @{b}CompressManager:   Short Help on the GUI@{ub}

   A simple call of the EASys!-Compressmanager will give you the choice
   of several Archiving-Functions/Applications.

   Calling the CompressManager, supplying arguments (Files), it will act
   as if the Function "Choose File(s)" would have been processed,
   which is described in the following text:


   @{b}Choose File(s)@{ub}

   will show up a FileList Requester. By simultaneously activating
   the left shift key and the left MouseButton, you may choose (mark)
   all files which you want to pack to an archive / de-archive.

   If only ONE File has been chosen, containing a Suffix .arj .arc .dms
   .lha .lzh .lzx .tar .zip .zoo), then the appropriate unpacking
   dialog will be startet and shown.

   If only ONE File WITHOUT such a suffix or GENERALLY SEVERAL Files
   have been selected, then an Archiving-dialog will be started,
   providing various Archive-Types for compressing.



   @{b}The newly created Archive@{ub} will generally contain the Directory
   as Parent directory, which is represented by it's original File's
   relative Directory in the original Directory tree:

   "DH0:Prog/Prog.doc"  will get a De-archiving-Path
   "Prog/Prog.doc"      after Archiving.

   This Directory "Prog", described in this example, will
   automatically be unpacked to "Temp:Prog/" if you would have
   chosen "Temp:" to be the unpacking destination directory
   in the EASys!-CompressManager unpacking Dialog.



   @{b}The Buttons ...@{ub}

   I think, it couldn't be more than it is: Self explanatory ...

   lha  Pressing this button, the CompressManager will call an externally
        located utility for working with LHA Archives.  ( please supply
        ${RefTable/Archive-guiLHA}  with a correct Path using the EASys!-
        ReferencePrefs Editor!   e.g. LhA-GUI by Brian D. King).

   Zip  see lha, but thought for  pkZip  (not compatible with WinZip!).
        Reference:  ${RefTable/Archive-guiPKAZIP}

   UU   ... Utility for working with UU-coded Mail-Files.
        Reference:  ${RefTable/Archive-guiUU}

   xpk  ... AppIcon-Utility for xpk / xfh-packed Files
        Reference:  ${RefTable/Archive-xpkDropper}



   @{b}Generally, ...@{ub}

   please supply a ToolManager-Dock for your Workbench,
   using the ToolManagerPrefs, entering a Shell-started entry

   ${RefTable/Archive-Manager}    including Argument-Handover.

   This Dock may then be used for dropping Files (Icons), which,
   in return will result in the described EASys! CompressManager
   Dialogs.

   While dropping Icons from Workbench, please note, that depending
   on Path-Length and count of arguments (Icons), argument passing
   is limited by the operating system! So, if no Dialog will show up
   after dropping Icons, just start the CompressManager itself by
   simply clicking it's Dock, and then call "Choose File(s)".
   Then, choose the Files you want to process.

   Using the FileRequester, no limits will prevent your work.



   @{b}Please, remember, using the File-Request in the CompressManager:@{ub}

   ONE file WITHOUT Archive-Suffix or generally SEVERAL selected
   Files will show up an Archiving (compressing) Dialog.

   ONE File including an Archive-Suffix (.arj .arc .dms .lha .lzh
   .lzx .tar .zip .zoo) will offer an un-archiving (decompressing)
   Dialog, including a choice for a destination-directory.

   Archives, dropped over as Argument directly from AMINET-CDs
   will show up a special dialog, which automatically will unpack
   to a temporary Test-Directory in RAM: .. then showing up the
   PresentationManager for exploring the Test-Directory .. and
   cleaning up the temporary directory after you will have
   exited the presentation.


